Not bad.

757
00:37:25,110 --> 00:37:28,762
♪ <i>But in the dark I
could not breathe</i> ♪

758
00:37:31,232 --> 00:37:36,202
♪ <i>I screamed until
I had no voice</i> ♪

759
00:37:36,237 --> 00:37:39,789
♪ <i>I screamed and then I had</i> ♪

760
00:37:39,825 --> 00:37:41,257
♪ <i>No choice...</i> ♪

761
00:37:41,293 --> 00:37:43,592
So you couldn't tell me
before that Rhys was here,

762
00:37:43,628 --> 00:37:45,289
but now you can
tell the whole world?

763
00:37:45,313 --> 00:37:46,779
I didn't call them.

764
00:37:46,814 --> 00:37:49,115
Bell probably wanted
his philanthropy televised.

765
00:37:49,167 --> 00:37:52,335
He always brings out his
best self in front of the cameras.

766
00:37:57,442 --> 00:38:00,460
Forgiving patient bills
won't cost us much.

767
00:38:00,495 --> 00:38:03,096
How much will the
other hospitals lose?

768
00:38:03,148 --> 00:38:04,948
Millions.

769
00:38:04,983 --> 00:38:09,285
And I hear the EMT lounge
you're building puts theirs to shame.

770
00:38:09,321 --> 00:38:11,754
Oh, it'll pay for
itself in a month.

771
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:13,418
How about Gordon?

772
00:38:13,442 --> 00:38:16,242
I'm closing in on him.

773
00:38:16,278 --> 00:38:19,195
♪ <i>Home again</i> ♪

774
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:23,333
♪ <i>I screamed</i> ♪

775
00:38:23,368 --> 00:38:26,486
♪ <i>Until I had no voice</i> ♪

776
00:38:26,538 --> 00:38:28,254
♪ <i>I screamed</i> ♪

777
00:38:28,289 --> 00:38:32,341
♪ <i>And then I had no choice</i> ♪

778
00:38:32,376 --> 00:38:36,262
♪ <i>Signs along the
road are hard to see...</i> ♪

779
00:38:36,298 --> 00:38:39,944
- How's Josh?
- Not out of the woods yet.

780
00:38:39,968 --> 00:38:43,353
At least he has
a fighting chance.

781
00:38:43,388 --> 00:38:45,104
♪ <i>Hey</i> ♪

782
00:38:45,140 --> 00:38:48,291
♪ <i>Carry me back,
carry me back...</i> ♪

783
00:38:48,326 --> 00:38:52,194
You only came to that
festival to see me, didn't you?

784
00:38:52,230 --> 00:38:54,190
Because I volunteered
on our day off.

785
00:38:54,215 --> 00:38:55,543
That's not true.
I love live music.

786
00:38:55,567 --> 00:38:57,449
You never go with me.

787
00:38:57,485 --> 00:39:00,686
'Cause you sway the whole
time. It's like being on a boat.

788
00:39:00,739 --> 00:39:02,467
- It's annoying.
- I do not sway.

789
00:39:02,491 --> 00:39:04,957
You're a swayer.

790
00:39:04,992 --> 00:39:06,525
Really?

791
00:39:06,578 --> 00:39:08,878
Yeah.

792
00:39:08,913 --> 00:39:11,347
All right, well, now
you're swaying.

793
00:39:11,382 --> 00:39:15,301
♪ <i>From myself...</i> ♪

794
00:39:15,336 --> 00:39:17,970
I won't make the same
mistakes. I will make time for us.

795
00:39:18,006 --> 00:39:19,389
We're busy.

796
00:39:19,424 --> 00:39:23,676
We both know what we
signed up for, but I will, too.

797
00:39:23,729 --> 00:39:27,230
♪ <i>Set me free</i> ♪

798
00:39:27,265 --> 00:39:30,216
♪ <i>Yeah, you...</i> ♪

799
00:39:30,252 --> 00:39:32,663
<i>Every day, doctors
make decisions.</i>

800
00:39:32,687 --> 00:39:35,905
Sometimes they're hard,
sometimes they're easy, but...

801
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:39,875
this is one of the easy ones.

802
00:39:39,911 --> 00:39:42,111
Josh is here
because I took a risk.

803
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:47,450
I broke a rule to save a life,
and if I hadn't, he'd be dead.

804
00:39:50,622 --> 00:39:52,622
But...

805
00:39:55,543 --> 00:39:56,876
you know that.

806
00:40:01,633 --> 00:40:03,449
We're done here.

807
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:25,588
You were right.

808
00:40:25,623 --> 00:40:29,793
And it's time I stop
telling you what to do.

809
00:40:29,828 --> 00:40:31,927
Will this be harder
to win at trial? Yes.

810
00:40:31,963 --> 00:40:36,115
But we are both fighters.
We will win this your way, son.

811
00:40:36,168 --> 00:40:38,767
And I will be with you
every step of the way,

812
00:40:38,804 --> 00:40:41,153
if you will let me.

813
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,643
Thank you.

814
00:41:08,867 --> 00:41:11,668
I get it.

815
00:41:11,703 --> 00:41:15,338
A doctor saves you,
you come home grateful,

816
00:41:15,373 --> 00:41:18,824
but rehab gets
hard, money dries up

817
00:41:18,877 --> 00:41:20,827
and your future
doesn't look like

818
00:41:20,879 --> 00:41:23,295
you hoped it would.
Soon, the doctor

819
00:41:23,348 --> 00:41:26,266
who stuck his neck
out to save your ass

820
00:41:26,301 --> 00:41:27,861
starts to represent
an opportunity.

821
00:41:27,885 --> 00:41:29,802
It's not personal.

822
00:41:29,855 --> 00:41:32,638
It is for me. Conrad's my son.

823
00:41:32,691 --> 00:41:35,841
So here's what happens next.

824
00:41:35,894 --> 00:41:40,680
I am having a nondisclosure
agreement drawn up as we speak.

825
00:41:40,715 --> 00:41:43,032
It will be delivered
to you within the hour,

826
00:41:43,067 --> 00:41:45,151
along with a generous check.

827
00:41:45,186 --> 00:41:48,203
It is an off-the-record
settlement

828
00:41:48,239 --> 00:41:51,524
that Conrad will
never know about.

829
00:41:51,559 --> 00:41:53,042
You will sign it.

830
00:41:53,077 --> 00:41:55,879
My son will be in the
cafeteria getting a coffee

831
00:41:55,914 --> 00:41:58,130
before his next shift.

832
00:41:58,165 --> 00:42:01,200
You are going to go
find him, apologize,

833
00:42:01,253 --> 00:42:05,221
tell him you will not
be taking a dime,

834
00:42:05,256 --> 00:42:07,390
shake his hand, and leave.

835
00:42:07,425 --> 00:42:09,392
- And if I don't?
- Mr. Robinson,

836
00:42:09,427 --> 00:42:13,229
I am a man of almost
unlimited means,

837
00:42:13,265 --> 00:42:15,514
and I will use them
to keep you in court

838
00:42:15,550 --> 00:42:18,067
the rest of your natural life.

839
00:42:18,102 --> 00:42:20,519
Now, you seem like a nice kid.

840
00:42:20,572 --> 00:42:23,722
I would hate to see
you broke, on the street,

841
00:42:23,757 --> 00:42:27,993
buried in legal bills
you cannot afford to pay.

842
00:42:28,028 --> 00:42:29,662
Because the truth is,

843
00:42:29,698 --> 00:42:33,749
you can't win a
lawsuit that never ends.

844
00:42:33,785 --> 00:42:38,704
So, the next time
someone saves your life,

845
00:42:38,757 --> 00:42:41,557
just... say thank you.

846
00:42:56,808 --> 00:42:58,791
♪ ♪

847
